The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Thursday, August 05, 2004  Business Briefs																								 Calcutta, Aug. 4: Texmaco Ltd, a KK Birla group company, said today it would spend over Rs 30 crore on modernisation and expansion of its steel-foundry division in the next 18 months. The steel-foundry division will undertake a major modernisation-cum-expansion programme, which will rank it as a state-of-the-art facility with the best internationally, said president Ramesh Maheswari. Following this, the divisions capacity would increase to 18,000 tonnes from 9,000 tonnes at present.																								 Bangalore, Aug. 4: Cable and Wireless (C amp;W), a British telecom firm, said it would invest $10 million in expanding its Indian operations over the next 18 months. Asia-Japan CEO Phil Green said about $5 million would be spent on expanding nodes and bandwidth, while an equal amount would be invested in people and infrastructure.																								 Hyderabad, Aug. 4: Global Trust Bank (GTB) will hold its board meeting on August 9 to consider the audited financial results for the financial year ended March 31, 2004. The meeting was earlier scheduled for today, the bank said.																								 New Delhi, Aug. 4: Union fertiliser and chemicals minister Ram Vilas Paswan today said the government is planning to bring about 300 more drugs under price control. 																								 New Delhi, Aug. 4: eBay today completed acquisition of Indian auction site, bazee.com, under which it acquired all outstanding shares of bazee.com Inc.
